to crate a hidden file using ls command :


windows :
Type attrib +h folder name to make your folder hidden from everyone.
To make it visible again, remove the hidden attribute using attrib -h folder_name./

$ touch soumaia.txt
$ attrib +h soumaia.txt
$ attrib -h soumaia.txt

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


to create multiple nested directories with one mkdir command.
$ sudo mkdir x/y/z


$ mkdir -p /c/usres/unmesh/these/folder/are/just/for/fun


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Verify number of characters in the file.



$ echo "hello" > fun
$ echo "i am soumaia" >> fun


$ wc -c fun
19 fun

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

to append something in the file *WITHOUT* a newline character:

$ echo "hello" > fun

$ echo -n "good morning" > fun

$ cat fun
